data.description: Welcome to 811 Bradley Street, West Hempstead - where nostalgia meets opportunity! Step into a time capsule of the groovy 70s, where wood paneling and shag carpeting create a canvas for your imagination. Unveil the hidden charm with beautiful hardwood floors beneath the carpet, just waiting for your personal touch.  This home boasts a unique history, having been lovingly crafted in 1958 by its original (and only) owner, who poured their heart into every detail. With solid bones and ample potential, it awaits your creative vision.  Enter the spacious sunken living room, a cozy retreat perfect for relaxing evenings. The formal dining room with sliders leading out to a paved patio, ideal for al fresco dining or entertaining under the stars. Three generously sized bedrooms offer comfort and space for your family to grow, while the full walkout basement with an additional room, full bathroom, spacious recreation area with bar and large closets, provides endless possibilities for customization.  Storage will never be an issue with loads of closets throughout the house, including a cedar closet, walk in closet and four additional closets in the basement alone, along with an attached one-car garage and outdoor shed. Enjoy the convenience of a concrete backyard, perfect for low-maintenance outdoor living.  The kitchen, a hub of activity, invites culinary adventures with its eat-in layout. Practical updates abound, including blown insulation, 5/8 sheetrock, central vaccum, inground sprinkler system, a roof just 4-5 years young, and a new gas burner and hot water tank installed just one year ago. With gas heating and electric cooking, comfort and efficiency are assured. This 1945 square foot home offers modern convenience in a classic setting.  Located just moments away from the Long Island Rail Road, parks, shops, and houses of worship, this home offers the perfect blend of convenience and tranquility. Don't miss your chance to make 811 Bradley Street your own - seize this opportunity to create the home of your dreams in the heart of West Hempstead.
